"{\"uid\": \"theatlantic.com-ideas-archive-2024-08-olympics-sore-losers-679390\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Sports have always had sore losers.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 35, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But based on this year's Games, athletes seem to be getting worse at losing well.\", \"from\": 36, \"to\": 117, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You would have forgiven Akio Kaminaga for losing his cool.\", \"from\": 119, \"to\": 177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 143, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akio_Kaminaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akio Kaminaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akio_Kaminaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akio_Kaminaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Heading into the gold-medal match at the Tokyo Olympics in 1964, the Japanese judo champion was under enormous pressure.\", \"from\": 178, \"to\": 298, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 247, \"end\": 255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.9453489298832579, \"rank\": 0.05778071676146823, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That year's Games heralded Japan's comeback after its wartime defeat, and judo, in particular, was a symbol of national pride.\", \"from\": 299, \"to\": 425, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 326, \"end\": 331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999859714991, \"rank\": 1.379299693830316e-08, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Japanese judo team was on the verge of sweeping all of the medals.\", \"from\": 426, \"to\": 496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 430, \"end\": 438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.9453489298832579, \"rank\": 0.05778071676146823, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kaminaga just needed one more victory-against a giant Dutchman named Antonius Geesink, who stood eight inches taller than him.\", \"from\": 497, \"to\": 623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 551, \"end\": 559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\", \"score\": 0.6970519778345569, \"rank\": 0.43461322697429283, \"text\": \"Dutchman\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_people\"}, {\"begin\": 566, \"end\": 574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Antony\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0358959656779734e-18, \"text\": \"Antonius\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Antony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Antony\"}, {\"begin\": 575, \"end\": 582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anton_Geesink\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Geesink\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anton_Geesink\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anton_Geesink\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kaminagalostto Geesink in two minutes.\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 663, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 640, \"end\": 647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anton_Geesink\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Geesink\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anton_Geesink\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anton_Geesink\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The arena was shocked; some people cried.\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 705, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, Kaminaga bowed to Geesink, smiled, and shook his hand.\", \"from\": 706, \"to\": 767, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the press began to swarm the competition floor, Geesink waved them off to spare Kaminaga the embarrassment.\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 878, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's remembered as a moment of sportsmanship and mutual respect.\", \"from\": 879, \"to\": 943, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The judo scene at this year's Olympics is unlikely to be recalled so fondly.\", \"from\": 945, \"to\": 1021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last week in Paris, the Japanese star Ryuju Nagayamarefusedto shake his opponent's hand after a loss.\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1123, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1035, \"end\": 1040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.283835152170832e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1046, \"end\": 1054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.9453489298832579, \"rank\": 0.05778071676146823, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Uta Abe, the defending women's gold medalist,shriekedon the sidelines for several minutes after losing in the second round.\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1247, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1124, \"end\": 1131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uta_Abe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Uta Abe\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uta_Abe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uta_Abe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most egregious of all, the Georgian judoka Guram Tushishvilireactedto defeat by kicking France's Teddy Riner in the crotch and then pushing his head into the mat, earning himself a red card and disqualification.\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1459, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1336, \"end\": 1342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7189608379840884, \"rank\": 0.3908404459869237, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1345, \"end\": 1356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Teddy Riner\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Devin Gordon: How sports got so whiny  And that's in a sport thatprizes etiquette.\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1467, \"end\": 1473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"score\": 0.99999999644524, \"rank\": 3.3461954394077137e-09, \"text\": \"Gordon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere, the Georgian fencer Sandro Bazadzethrewa fit after his loss, berating the referee, repeatedly yelling \\\"shame,\\\" and refusing to leave the piste while the crowd booed.\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1720, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1559, \"end\": 1567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgians\", \"score\": 0.7673851728185824, \"rank\": 0.3031044203446663, \"text\": \"Georgian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Georgians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The American tennis player Emma Navarro exchangedtense wordswith her victorious opponent, China's Qinwen Zheng.\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1832, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1725, \"end\": 1733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999999913598, \"rank\": 8.59141299620164e-12, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1748, \"end\": 1760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Navarro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma Navarro\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Navarro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Navarro\"}, {\"begin\": 1811, \"end\": 1816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9705814850189904, \"rank\": 0.030309225824474668, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1826, \"end\": 1831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Jie\", \"score\": 0.8445727067456729, \"rank\": 0.18402150775425768, \"text\": \"Zheng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Jie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Jie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I just told her I did not respect her as a competitor,\\\" Navarro said to reporters.\", \"from\": 1833, \"to\": 1916, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1890, \"end\": 1897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jaime_Navarro\", \"score\": 0.9999999673332246, \"rank\": 2.7065543497120056e-08, \"text\": \"Navarro\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jaime_Navarro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jaime_Navarro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their Polish competitor Iga Swiatek, the top-rated women's player in the world, could not handle losing to Zheng either,refusingto shake hands with the chair umpire and skipping several of her obligatory post-match interviews.\", \"from\": 1917, \"to\": 2143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1923, \"end\": 1929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland\", \"score\": 0.9598103132694601, \"rank\": 0.04158231643076747, \"text\": \"Polish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland\"}, {\"begin\": 1941, \"end\": 1944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.403834317916547e-21, \"text\": \"Iga\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\"}, {\"begin\": 2024, \"end\": 2029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Jie\", \"score\": 0.8445727067456729, \"rank\": 0.18402150775425768, \"text\": \"Zheng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Jie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zheng_Jie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports has always had sore losers.\", \"from\": 2145, \"to\": 2179, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"John McEnroe made an art of it.\", \"from\": 2180, \"to\": 2211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2180, \"end\": 2192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_McEnroe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"John McEnroe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_McEnroe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_McEnroe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No one at Paris 2024 has yet bitten their opponent's ear off.\", \"from\": 2212, \"to\": 2273, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But based on this year's Games, athletes seem to be getting worse at losing well.\", \"from\": 2274, \"to\": 2355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As with most sports stories, this one appears to be about more than sports.\", \"from\": 2356, \"to\": 2431, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whether in politics, business, or culture, dignity in defeat is going out of fashion.\", \"from\": 2432, \"to\": 2517, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not just in our head.In a 2017 survey of referees in the United States, 57 percent said that sportsmanship was getting worse.\", \"from\": 2519, \"to\": 2649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2581, \"end\": 2594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999992454370958, \"rank\": 7.520486749505125e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By 2023, that number had climbed to 69 percent, and half said they'd at some point feared for their safety.\", \"from\": 2650, \"to\": 2757, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think society as a whole has moved away from good sportspersonship,\\\" David Matsumoto, a former Olympic judo coach and a psychology professor at San Francisco State University, told me.\", \"from\": 2758, \"to\": 2945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2830, \"end\": 2845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Matsumoto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David Matsumoto\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Matsumoto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Matsumoto\"}, {\"begin\": 2905, \"end\": 2924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_State_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.3480927894213994e-21, \"text\": \"San Francisco State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_State_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/San_Francisco_State_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The main culprit, according to some experts, is increasing pressure.\", \"from\": 2947, \"to\": 3015, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Young athletes start earlier and spend more time training than in the past.\", \"from\": 3016, \"to\": 3091, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More money is at stake too: Sponsors reward success even in obscure sports such as handball and artistic swimming, and many athletes make an income asinfluencers.\", \"from\": 3092, \"to\": 3254, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A number of countries pay their Olympic athletes, with big bonuses for medaling.\", \"from\": 3255, \"to\": 3335, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Losing the gold can mean losing gold.\", \"from\": 3336, \"to\": 3373, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Boorish athletes might also be reacting to growing amounts of attention.\", \"from\": 3375, \"to\": 3447, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stephen Garcia, a psychologist at the University of Michigan who studies competition, told me that athletes often suffer \\\"evaluation apprehension\\\" based on the number of people watching them.\", \"from\": 3448, \"to\": 3639, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3448, \"end\": 3462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Garcia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephen Garcia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Garcia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Garcia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bigger the audience, the more stress they feel.\", \"from\": 3640, \"to\": 3691, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now that anyone with a phone can broadcast an event in real time, and highlights (and lowlights) live on in social-media feeds, the feeling of being watched is more powerful than ever, Garcia said.\", \"from\": 3692, \"to\": 3889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3877, \"end\": 3883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerry_Garcia\", \"score\": 0.9999997316172444, \"rank\": 2.683827847511076e-07, \"text\": \"Garcia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerry_Garcia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerry_Garcia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another possibility: People everywhere are becoming more selfish.\", \"from\": 3891, \"to\": 3956, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Studies have shown that as countries get richer, their citizens become more individualistic.\", \"from\": 3957, \"to\": 4049, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Because good sportsmanship is largely about subordinating one's own emotions for the sake of the group, Matsumoto said, it follows that a decline in collectivist thinking could lead to more blowups.\", \"from\": 4050, \"to\": 4248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4154, \"end\": 4163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matsumoto_Domain\", \"score\": 0.9986771550354989, \"rank\": 0.0013245917487327088, \"text\": \"Matsumoto\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matsumoto_Domain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matsumoto_Domain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The lack of self-regulation extends beyond sports.\", \"from\": 4250, \"to\": 4300, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The sorest loser of all needs no introduction.\", \"from\": 4301, \"to\": 4347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Donald Trump's refusal to accept the results of the 2020 election was unprecedented at the time.\", \"from\": 4348, \"to\": 4444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4348, \"end\": 4360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.073714796980492e-16, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since then, voicing doubts about elections has become contagious within the Republican Party.\", \"from\": 4445, \"to\": 4538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4521, \"end\": 4537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Dakota_Republican_Party\", \"score\": 0.7341019263357209, \"rank\": 0.36063080650428286, \"text\": \"Republican Party\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Dakota_Republican_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/North_Dakota_Republican_Party\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 2022 midterms, a raft of GOP candidatesrefused to concedetheir losses.\", \"from\": 4539, \"to\": 4616, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4571, \"end\": 4574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republican_Party_of_Texas\", \"score\": 0.9995686584661834, \"rank\": 0.0004315276690397499, \"text\": \"GOP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republican_Party_of_Texas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republican_Party_of_Texas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Trump has also rejected the court decisions against him-one jury found him civilly liable for sexual abuse, another criminally guilty of falsifying business records-as illegitimate.\", \"from\": 4617, \"to\": 4798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4617, \"end\": 4622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.538762732590469e-14, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The generous take is that stubbornness is less about lying than about projecting strength.\", \"from\": 4799, \"to\": 4889, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Hillary Clinton \\\"fought on\\\" in the 2008 primaries long past the point of having any chance of beating Barack Obama.)\", \"from\": 4890, \"to\": 5007, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4891, \"end\": 4906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hillary_Clinton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.606218681800602e-14, \"text\": \"Hillary Clinton\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hillary_Clinton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hillary_Clinton\"}, {\"begin\": 4993, \"end\": 5005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barack_Obama\", \"score\": 0.9999999973429112, \"rank\": 2.656614971537334e-09, \"text\": \"Barack Obama\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barack_Obama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barack_Obama\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Or perhaps it's theShaggy theoryof denial: Say it enough times, and people will believe it.\", \"from\": 5008, \"to\": 5099, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From the November 2022 issue: Bad losers  There is no L bigger than death, and we are trying to avoid that too.\", \"from\": 5101, \"to\": 5212, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Venture-capital funds are investingbillionsin longevity research.\", \"from\": 5213, \"to\": 5278, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rich people are paying to have themselvesfrozenwhen they die, and even if their body expires, AI promises topreservetheir digital self.\", \"from\": 5279, \"to\": 5414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5373, \"end\": 5375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.9999999981196197, \"rank\": 1.8803759068270765e-09, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We never have to say goodbye to our cultural idols, either: Thanks to hologram technology, we can watchAbbaandElvisand someday, probably, Post Malone in concert for the rest of our eternal life.\", \"from\": 5415, \"to\": 5609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5553, \"end\": 5564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Post_Malone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.280638012437132e-39, \"text\": \"Post Malone\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Post_Malone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Post_Malone\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In some contexts, there is beauty in refusing to accept loss.\", \"from\": 5611, \"to\": 5672, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Raging against the dying of the light can be moving, even inspiring.\", \"from\": 5673, \"to\": 5741, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Death, be not proud,\\\" we say, ignoring the Grim Reaper's undefeated record.\", \"from\": 5742, \"to\": 5818, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When it comes to sports, however, denying reality is not poetic; it's just dumb.\", \"from\": 5820, \"to\": 5900, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletics is one of the few realms in life where the results are definitive.\", \"from\": 5901, \"to\": 5977, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's why we watch: The finality is the point.\", \"from\": 5978, \"to\": 6025, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A society that can not accept losing in sports is not equipped to handle more difficult truths.\", \"from\": 6026, \"to\": 6121, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TheAtlantic.com \\u00a92026The Atlantic Monthly Group.\", \"from\": 6123, \"to\": 6171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6148, \"end\": 6164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlantic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Atlantic Monthly\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlantic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlantic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 6172, \"to\": 6192, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and the GooglePrivacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply\", \"from\": 6194, \"to\": 6282, \"entities\": []}]}"